  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nAs per [this thread](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/2888#issuecomment-1008438208), it seems to make sense to delay switching back to a BN after it comes back online (e.g., if primary was offline but came back online). This allows the BN to get itself in order and acts as a bit of a \"debounce\".\r\n\r\nI propose a 2-3 epoch delay.\r\n",
